<body>

<div class="canvas">

  <div class="column">
    <h2 class="saas-title">Traditional SaaS / Managed Service</h2>
    <div class="sub-title">Centralized Trust & Vendor Dependency</div>

    <div class="node saas-box saas-bg">
      <strong>DEPLOYMENT MODEL</strong>
      <span>Customer data is processed and stored on the **Vendor's Cloud**.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="arrow saas-arrow">↓</div>

    <div class="node saas-box">
      <strong>TRUST IN THE VENDOR</strong>
      <span>Integrity relies on the vendor's legal contracts, security team, and internal audits.</span>
      <div style="margin-top:10px;">
        <span class="saas-detail">Vendor is a central point of control and failure.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="arrow saas-arrow">↓</div>

    <div class="node saas-box saas-bg">
      <strong>SUBSCRIPTION & VISIBILITY</strong>
      <span>Billing is subscription-based (per user/month). Vendor sees all metadata/usage data.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="arrow saas-arrow">↓</div>

    <div class="core-diff core-teal">
      <strong>CORE RISK: CUSTODIAL TRUST</strong>
      <span>The customer must continuously trust the vendor not to fail, collude, or have a catastrophic security breach.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="column">
    <h2 class="novak-title">NOVAK Protocol</h2>
    <div class="sub-title">Decentralized Verification & Mathematical Trust</div>

    <div class="node novak-box novak-bg">
      <strong>DEPLOYMENT MODEL</strong>
      <span>The integrity engine runs **within the Customer's environment** (on-prem or private cloud).</span>
    </div>
    <div class="arrow novak-arrow">↓</div>

    <div class="node novak-box">
      <strong>TRUST IN THE MATH</strong>
      <span>Integrity relies on the SHA-256 algorithm and the unbreakable **REVELATION** chain.</span>
      <div style="margin-top:10px;">
        <span class="novak-detail">System integrity is mathematically enforced and auditable.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="arrow novak-arrow">↓</div>

    <div class="node novak-box novak-bg">
      <strong>PROTOCOL FEE & SEGREGATION</strong>
      <span>Cost is per-execution/per-hash. NOVAK only sees the non-sensitive **HARMONEE** proof (the hash).</span>
    </div>
    <div class="arrow novak-arrow">↓</div>

    <div class="core-diff core-purple">
      <strong>CORE STRENGTH: NON-CUSTODIAL TRUST</strong>
      <span>The integrity layer is physically and cryptographically separate from the vendor, removing single points of failure and trust requirements.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

